net.cloud.gfx.elements

Class RadioButton.RadioButtonGroup

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.cloud.gfx.elements.RadioButton.RadioButtonGroup
  • Enclosing class:
    RadioButton

    public static class RadioButton.RadioButtonGroup
extends java.lang.Object
    A logical grouping of Radio Buttons. Controls some of the behaviors, such as enforcing selection of one at a time and linking them in a focus traversal chain.

    • Constructor Detail

      • RadioButtonGroup

        public RadioButtonGroup()
        Create a new RadioButtonGroup with no buttons in it, no currently selected button, and no action handler.
        Use add(RadioButton) to add buttons - in the order you want them.
        Use setSelected(int) to set which button is selected. Doing this after adding buttons is like setting a default.
        Use setActionHandler(Consumer) to set an action handler over the entire group.

    • Method Detail

      • getSelectedButton

        public RadioButton getSelectedButton()
        Returns:
        The button currently selected in the group. May be null.

      • getSelectedIndex

        public int getSelectedIndex()
        Returns:
        The index of the currently selected button. -1 if there is none.

      • setSelection

        public boolean setSelection(RadioButton newSelection)
        Finds the given button in the group and selects it. If the button is not in the group, then false is returned and nothing happens. This will trigger an event if a handler is set.
        Parameters:
        newSelection - The new button to make selected
        Returns:
        False if it was not in the group

      • setSelection

        public void setSelection(int index)
        Set a button in the group to be selected. If another button is already selected, it will be deselected. This will also trigger an event if there is a handler. Prefer this method over setSelection(RadioButton)
        Parameters:
        index - The 0 based index of the button

      • selectNext

        public void selectNext()
        Selects the next button in the group. Works in a circular fashion, so if the current button is the last, then the first button in the group will become selected. Of course, if there are no buttons or only one in the group, this will do nothing. This will trigger an action event.

      • selectPrevious

        public void selectPrevious()
        Selects the previous button in the group. Works in a circular fashion, so if the current button is the first, then the last button in the group will become selected. Of course, if there are no buttons or only one in the group, this will do nothing. This will trigger an action event.

      • add

        protected void add(RadioButton button)
        Add a button to this group. The button will be added to the end of the group (So add buttons in the order you want them in the group.) This will also establish a focus chain within the group. The first and last buttons will not have previous and next elements, respectively. However, there will be links established within the group itself. They are not maintained and may be reset if need be.
        Parameters:
        button - The button to append to the group

      • buttonAction

        protected void buttonAction(RadioButton actedUpon)
        Called when a button has an action performed on it.
        Parameters:
        actedUpon - The button that had the action happen

      • setActionHandler

        public void setActionHandler(java.util.function.Consumer<RadioButton.RadioButtonEvent> action)
        Set a new action to this group. When a button's state is changed within the group, the action's method will be called and supply information about what happened. By providing null as a parameter to this method, you may remove the current handler.
        Parameters:
        action - The method to call when action is taken on this button
